2. EMBEDDED CODE SAMPLES AND SPHINX MACHINERY

   The following are licensed under the MIT License:

   - All code samples embedded in prose, including literal blocks
     and the contents of any `.. code-block::` directive.
   - The Sphinx configuration (`source/conf.py`).
   - The Sphinx extensions (`source/_ext/*.py`).
   - The auxiliary tooling (`tools/*.py`).
   - The build glue (`Makefile`, `make.bat`).

   The full text of the MIT License is reproduced below.

   Rationale: a reader copy-pasting a 10-line example into their own
   proprietary code must be unambiguously allowed to do so. CC-BY's
   attribution requirement is well suited to prose excerpts but
   creates friction for short code snippets in a build pipeline.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

